title: Head of an Ibis
description:
One bronze head of an ibis. There are bone inlays in the eyes. It bears an incised line broad collar at the base of the neck.

Condition: Black/Cu patina. Eyes are of bone inlay much cracked on the right side. Chip is missing from atop head. Casting flaw left side of head. Solid cast on good condition.
